@startuml sealed-secrets-lifecycle
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

skinparam participant {
    BackgroundColor #EEF4FF
    BorderColor #4A6FA5
    FontColor #1A1A2E
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFF9E6
    BorderColor #D4A017
}

title Sealed Secrets Lifecycle

actor Developer
participant "bootstrap.sh" as Bootstrap
participant "Sealed Secrets\nController" as Controller order 30
participant "Git Repo" as Git order 40
participant "Kubernetes" as K8s order 50

== One-time Setup ==

Developer -> Bootstrap : run after tofu apply
Bootstrap -> Controller : fetch public cert\n(kubeseal --fetch-cert)
Controller --> Bootstrap : sealed-secrets-dev.pem
Bootstrap -> Git : commit k8s/certs/sealed-secrets-dev.pem

note over Git : Public cert is safe to commit —\nonly the controller holds the private key

== Sealing a Secret ==

Developer -> Developer : kubectl create secret ... --dry-run -o yaml\n| kubeseal --cert sealed-secrets-dev.pem
Developer -> Git : commit SealedSecret YAML\n(encrypted ciphertext)

== In-Cluster Decryption (ArgoCD sync-wave -1) ==

Git -> K8s : ArgoCD applies SealedSecret\n(wave -1, before Deployments)
K8s -> Controller : SealedSecret resource created/updated
Controller -> Controller : decrypt using private key\n(never leaves cluster)
Controller -> K8s : create standard Secret

note over K8s : Deployments (wave 0) start\nonly after Secrets exist

== Key Loss Recovery (after tofu destroy) ==

Developer -> Bootstrap : re-run bootstrap.sh
Bootstrap -> Controller : fetch new public cert
Controller --> Bootstrap : new sealed-secrets-dev.pem
Bootstrap -> Git : commit new cert + re-sealed SealedSecret YAMLs

note over Git : Old SealedSecrets are invalid after key rotation —\nbootstrap.sh re-seals and overwrites them

@enduml
